# Auth and storage

## Modes

| Context | Identity | Party room id |
|--------|-----------|----------------|
| Discord Activity | Embedded SDK + token Worker | `sdk.instanceId` or `ch-{channelId}` |
| `VITE_DISCORD_MOCK=1` | Fixed mock user | `mock-room` |
| Website (default) | `localStorage` `imposter-web-user-id` + display name in `imposter-web-display-name` | `sessionStorage` party room |
| Website + Supabase | Anonymous Supabase user id (`signInAnonymously`) | same session room |

## Env vars (client / build)

- `VITE_DISCORD_CLIENT_ID`, `VITE_PARTYKIT_HOST`, `VITE_DISCORD_TOKEN_URL` — Discord + Partykit.
- `VITE_SUPABASE_URL` plus any of `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_DEFAULT_KEY`, or `VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` — optional; enables anonymous auth + `web_profiles` upserts from `src/lib/web-session.ts` (see `src/lib/supabase-client.ts`).
- `VITE_DISCORD_MOCK` — force mock.

## Supabase setup

1. Create project; enable **Authentication → Anonymous sign-ins**.
2. Run `supabase/migrations/001_web_profiles.sql` (CLI `db push` or SQL editor).
3. Set `VITE_SUPABASE_*` in `.env` locally and in Cloudflare Pages build env.

## Post-deploy checklist

See `docs/POST_LAUNCH.md`. Deploy order: Worker secrets → Partykit → Pages build with all `VITE_*`.
